A populated place. A town located in the province and the autonomous community of Navarre, northern Spain.

One of the 23 provinces of Argentina, located in the western central part of the country in the Cuyo region. Neighboring provinces are from the north clockwise San Juan, San Luis, La Pampa,and Neuquen. To the west is Chile.

A populated place. in New South Wales.

A province on the southern coast of China. Guangdong borders Fujian province to the northeast, Jiangxi and Hunan provinces to the north, Guangxi autonomous region to the west, and Hong Kong and Macau Special Administrative Regions to the south. Hainan province is offshore across from the Leizhou Peninsula.

A province of the People's Republic of China located in the northeastern part of the country. Heilongjiang borders Jilin in the south and Inner Mongolia to the west; it also borders Russia to the north. The Amur River marks the border between the People's Republic of China and Russia to the north. Heilongjiang contains China's northernmost point (in Mohe County along the Amur) and easternmost point (at the junction of the Amur and Ussuri Rivers).

A canton of Switzerland. Appenzell Ausserrhoden is located in the north east of Switzerland, bordering the cantons of St. Gallen and Appenzell Innerrhoden. It has 20 municipalities (Einwohnergemeinden); formerly it was divided into 3 districts (Bezirke).
A canton in the north east of Switzerland. It has 6 Bezirke (districts).

One of the 26 cantons of Switzerland. The capital is Liestal. It shares borders with the cantons of Basel-Stadt, Solothurn, Jura and Aargau, and with France and the German State of Baden-Wurttemberg. There are 5 Bezirke in Basel-Landschaft.

A canton of Switzerland. It is located in the west of the country. The canton of Fribourg lies in the west of Switzerland. It is bounded to the west by the Lake Neuchatel. To the west and the south of the canton lies the canton of Vaud. To the east the canton of Fribourg is bounded by the canton of Bern. There are enclaves within the canton of Vaud. The Canton of Fribourg is divided into 7 districts and 168 municipalities.
A canton in east central Switzerland. The capital is Glarus. There are 25 municipalities (gemeinden) in the canton.

One of the Cantons of Switzerland. It is the newest (created in 1979) of the 26 Swiss cantons, located in the northwestern part of Switzerland. The capital is Delemont. It shares borders with the Canton of Basel-Landschaft, the Canton of Bern, and the French departement of Jura. It has 3 districts and 83 municipaities (communes).

The largest and easternmost canton of Switzerland. The canton borders on Liechtenstein to the north, Austria to the north and the east, Italy to the south and southeast, and the cantons of St. Gallen to the northwest, Canton of Glarus, Uri to the west, and Ticino to the southwest. The capital city is Chur. It is divided into 11 Districts. They tend to follow the natural boundaries of the landscape. The districts are further subdivided into 39 sub-districts (Kreise).

A canton of western Switzerland. The canton of Neuchatel is located in the west of Switzerland. To its northeast it borders the canton of Bern, the northwest France. The Lake Neuchatel lies southeast of the canton, while the canton of Vaud is southwest of the canton of Neuchatel. The canton lies in the central area of the Jura Mountains. Lake Neuchatel drains the lands in the south, whilst the River Doubs drains the northern areas.
A canton of Switzerland. It is located in the centre of Switzerland.
A canton of Switzerland. It is located in the centre of Switzerland. The Canton of Lucerne is divided into 5 districts termed Amter. There are 99 municipalities in the canton (as of 2006-01).

A canton in central Switzerland between Lake Lucerne in the south and Lake Zurich in the north, centered around and named after the town of Schwyz. The Canton of Schwyz is divided into six districts and 30 municipalities, although the districts Einsiedeln, Kussnacht and Gersau simply comprise the municipality of the same name.

A canton of Switzerland. The principal city and capital of the canton is Schaffhausen. The canton of Schaffhausen is the northernmost canton of Switzerland, located to the north of Zurich. It lies west of the Lake Constance. It is almost entirely surrounded by Germany, which lies to the north, east and west of the canton. The canton of Schaffhausen is even divided by parts of Germany. Prior to 1999-07 it was divided into 6 districts (Bezirke).
A canton of Switzerland. It is located in the centre of Switzerland. There are seven municipalities in the Canton.

A canton in Switzerland, in the southwestern part of the country, around the valley of the Rhone from its headwaters to Lake Geneva, separating the Pennine Alps from the Bernese Alps. To its south lies Italy, to the southwest France. To the north the canton is bounded by the Swiss cantons of Vaud and Bern; the cantons of Uri and Ticino lie to its east.
A canton of Switzerland located in Central Switzerland. The canton's territory covers the valley of the Reuss River between Lake Lucerne and the St. Gotthard Pass.

One of the 26 cantons of Switzerland. It is located in central Switzerland and its capital is Zug. The canton of Lucerne and Canton of Aargau lie to its west. To the north, the canton is bound by the Canton of Zurich, whereas to the west and south lies the Canton of Schwyz. It has 11 municipalities.

A canton of Switzerland. It is located in the northwest of Switzerland. The capital is Solothurn. The canton is located in the north west of Switzerland. To the west and south lies the canton of Bern, to the east the one of Aargau. To the north the canton is bound by the canton of Basel-Landschaft. Two of the districts are enclaves and are located along the French border. From 2005, Solothurn's ten districts are merged pairwise into five electoral districts, termed Amtei. From 2005, districts only have a statistical meaning. The canton has 125 municipalities (Einwohnergemeinden).
A populated place. A hamlet in De Witt, Onondaga County, New York, United States, part of the greater Syracuse area.
